===[ Feature Engineering in Time Series Data  ]================================
* Feature Engineering is the process of using domain knowledge to extract
  useful features from raw data, In time series analysis, effective feature
  engineering is crucial for capturing temporal dependencies and patterns, which
  can lead to better predictive performance and insights 

===[ Time Series Feature Engineering ]===

  1|> Lag Features: Capture past values of the time series to predict future
      values.
  
  2|> Rolling Statistics: Calculate statistics (mean, standard deviation) over 
      a rolling window

  3|> Fourier Transforms: Decompose the time series into frequency components. 

  4|> Handling Seasonality: Identify and adjust for seasonal pattern 

===[ Lag Features: ]=== 
* Since the 'past influence the future', we can simply use the past values to  
  help us predict the future, this is the main idea of lag features.  
  - Since the lag feature are correlated, we use different lags to help the  
    model capture the 'seasonality' (e.g. 1, 7, 14, 24, ...) 

  # NOTE:[ Lag Features Can be created for both 'Target' & 'Features' ]

# CONCLUSION: ]================================================================
# - Lag features are one of the 'most powerful tools' in time series modeling | 
# - because they allow your model to `see` the past behavior of the series    |
#   and learn temporal dependecies.                                           |
# - Most time series are autocorrelated - past values influence future ones,  |
#   lag features make this relationship explicit for models like:             |
#     . Linear Regression                                                     |
#     . Random Forests                                                        |
#     . XGBoost                                                               |
#     . Neural networks                                                       |
# > Without lag features, these models cannot inherently learn from the series|
# - A lag feature is the value of the target or feature k period(s) in the    | 
#   past: X(t - k)                                                            |
# =============================================================================

===[ Lag Feature-engine: `LagFeatures` class ]===
- Lag 'feature-engine' provides a class `LagFeatures` to create a transformer 

  # imports
  from feature_engine.timeseries.forecasting import LagFeatures

  # code: MS: Months
  lag_transformed = LagFeatures(variables=['y'], freq=['1MS', '2MS', '3MS'])
  lag_transformed.fit_transform(df)

  # Output
  - a dataFrame of target columns 
  _________________________________________________________
  | DateIndex  |  y  | y_lag_1MS | y_lag_2MS  | y_lag_3MS |
  |------------|-----|-----------|------------|-----------|
  | 2025-01-01 | ... |   NaN     |    NaN     |    NaN    |
  | 2025-02-01 | ... |   ...     |    NaN     |    NaN    |
  | 2025-03-01 | ... |   ...     |    ...     |    NaN    |
  | 2025-04-01 | ... |   ...     |    ...     |    ...    |
  | 2025-05-01 | ... |   ...     |    ...     |    ...    |
